249
00:11:20,235 --> 00:11:21,928
- I forgot my notes.
- I put them in your bedroom.

250
00:11:36,258 --> 00:11:38,228
- Hello?
- Hi, Mom.

251
00:11:39,094 --> 00:11:39,847
Lorelai?

252
00:11:40,123 --> 00:11:41,141
Yup, it's me.

253
00:11:43,271 --> 00:11:45,293
- So, how are you?
- I'm fine.

254
00:11:45,458 --> 00:11:46,747
Good. How's Dad?

255
00:11:46,943 --> 00:11:48,428
- He's fine.
- Also good.

256
00:11:48,638 --> 00:11:50,051
May I speak with Rory please?

257
00:11:50,194 --> 00:11:51,941
- No, you can't speak with Rory.
- Why not?

258
00:11:52,130 --> 00:11:53,768
- Because I called you.
- So what?

259
00:11:53,932 --> 00:11:56,094
You don't get to request a switch when a person calls you.

260
00:11:56,221 --> 00:11:57,864
I'm sure she's standing right there.

261
00:11:57,986 --> 00:12:00,614
Not the point. If you wanna talk to Rory, you have to call.

262
00:12:00,726 --> 00:12:02,646
Then when I answer the phone, you can ask for Rory.

263
00:12:02,743 --> 00:12:05,643
But you didn't call, I called, so you cannot ask for Rory.

264
00:12:05,801 --> 00:12:07,280
What do you want, Lorelai?

265
00:12:07,419 --> 00:12:09,907
I just wanted to see how you were. I haven't seen you for awhile.

266
00:12:10,117 --> 00:12:12,360
- Your choice.
- No, your choice, Mom.

267
00:12:12,503 --> 00:12:14,633
You're the one who called off Friday night dinners.

268
00:12:14,720 --> 00:12:17,132
No, I'm the one who called off the obligation for Friday night dinners.

269
00:12:17,234 --> 00:12:20,152
You're the one who called off... You know what, I didn't call to argue.

270
00:12:20,255 --> 00:12:21,418
Fine, let's not argue.

271
00:12:21,602 --> 00:12:22,999
Come on, Mom, this is silly.

272
00:12:23,553 --> 00:12:27,111
I mean, think back to before the whole Friday night dinner thing.

273
00:12:27,219 --> 00:12:28,571
We still had a relationship.

274
00:12:28,709 --> 00:12:30,685
You mean the one where I would trick you into calling me

275
00:12:30,783 --> 00:12:32,528
by leaving a message on your answering machine

276
00:12:32,642 --> 00:12:34,331
saying I had something important to tell you,

277
00:12:34,428 --> 00:12:37,055
but I wouldn't include the details so you had no choice but to call me.

278
00:12:37,689 --> 00:12:38,616
Yes.

279
00:12:38,801 --> 00:12:41,253
And then when you did call, we'd talk about the weather,

280
00:12:41,325 --> 00:12:43,973
you'd ask about the DAR, and then you'd put Rory on the phone,

281
00:12:44,080 --> 00:12:46,666
- even when she was too young to talk.
- It was not always like that.

282
00:12:46,800 --> 00:12:48,187
It was always like that.

283
00:12:48,539 --> 00:12:53,378
Very well. The weather's fine, the DAR is staging a luncheon at the library next week.

284
00:12:53,460 --> 00:12:55,351
You already said I couldn't talk to Rory, so there,

285
00:12:55,427 --> 00:12:58,095
- I think you've fulfilled your obligation.
- Okay, Mom, fine.

286
00:12:58,212 --> 00:12:59,738
- Have a nice day.
- Same to you.

287
00:13:05,324 --> 00:13:06,118
It's for you!

288
00:13:07,828 --> 00:13:09,815
- Sorry, sorry, sorry.
- The issue is a disaster.

289
00:13:09,983 --> 00:13:12,016
It's our last issue of the Franklin and it's a complete disaster.

290
00:13:12,130 --> 00:13:13,030
I'm sure it's not that bad.

291
00:13:13,118 --> 00:13:15,488
And that's why you won't need to Botox your frown lines on your nineteenth birthday.

292
00:13:15,555 --> 00:13:18,109
Not that picture, no, put it down. Put it down now!

293
00:13:18,529 --> 00:13:20,460
- How's it coming?
- Very frustrating.

294
00:13:20,564 --> 00:13:22,355
We just can't seem to get exactly the right combination.

295
00:13:22,932 --> 00:13:25,642
All right. How about blue dress, blonde guy, black limo? Works best for me.

296
00:13:25,801 --> 00:13:28,473
Yes, however, green dress, red-haired guy, white limo works best for me.

297
00:13:28,555 --> 00:13:31,008
White limo with blonde guy totally doesn't work. It's too washed up.

298
00:13:31,065 --> 00:13:33,414
I'm assuming this conversation veered off of the cover page placement?

299
00:13:33,578 --> 00:13:35,709
How about black-haired guy, green dress and tan limo?

300
00:13:35,959 --> 00:13:37,556
- Tan limo?
- Good neutral backdrop.

301
00:13:37,745 --> 00:13:40,645
Well, this opens up a whole new set of options. Bring the golf team back in.

302
00:13:40,736 --> 00:13:43,399
Okay, why don't I just get these pesky Franklin articles out of your way.

303
00:13:43,471 --> 00:13:44,780
- There we go.
- What are you doing?

304
00:13:44,908 --> 00:13:47,102
- I am working on the front page placement.
- What are they doing?

305
00:13:47,193 --> 00:13:49,483
- Staying true to who they are.
- Look, prom is once.

306
00:13:49,584 --> 00:13:51,581
It happens, it's photographed, and then it's there forever.

307
00:13:51,726 --> 00:13:52,739
Planning is essential.

308
00:13:52,861 --> 00:13:54,986
By the way, Paris, we left a space for you in the limo.

309
00:13:55,042 --> 00:13:56,301
However, we're gonna need the color of your dress.

310
00:13:56,393 --> 00:13:57,172
And a picture of Jamie.

311
00:13:57,258 --> 00:13:59,107
And the amount of flexibility that you have with the color of your dress.

312
00:13:59,200 --> 00:13:59,881
And with Jamie.

313
00:14:00,005 --> 00:14:01,792
Thank you, but we've already made our plans for prom night.

314
00:14:01,960 --> 00:14:03,947
Jamie hired a private car to drive us to the prom.

315
00:14:04,048 --> 00:14:06,982
We'll go in, take the picture, depending on the level of lameness, dance.

316
00:14:07,167 --> 00:14:10,070
Then he's taking me to dinner at Antoine's, followed by a helicopter ride to join

317
00:14:10,152 --> 00:14:11,965
his parents out in Martha's Vineyard for the weekend.

318
00:14:12,307 --> 00:14:14,361
- What color's the helicopter?
- As you were.

319
00:14:15,114 --> 00:14:17,141
So, have you figured out your plans for prom night yet?

320
00:14:17,275 --> 00:14:19,972
Oh, no, but Stars Hollow is a much more casual kind of a prom.

321
00:14:20,086 --> 00:14:22,251
- Less Cinderella, more Footloose.
- Still a prom.

322
00:14:22,436 --> 00:14:23,304
It is still a prom.

323
00:14:24,007 --> 00:14:24,677
I can't wait.

324
00:14:29,727 --> 00:14:33,429
It's my own fault. I poked a slumbering bear with a stick.

325
00:14:33,649 --> 00:14:37,991
I reached out and initiated contact with Emily Gilmore. I get what I deserve.

326
00:14:38,175 --> 00:14:40,403
- You're a bad girl.
- You know what really stinks?

327
00:14:40,592 --> 00:14:43,153
They're having Rory over tonight for a movie night.

328
00:14:43,280 --> 00:14:44,883
Movie night? That's your thing with her.

329
00:14:45,006 --> 00:14:46,497
Exactly. What's next?

330
00:14:46,802 --> 00:14:50,239
"Stay home and dance around in your underwear to the Monkees' greatest hits" night?

331
00:14:50,315 --> 00:14:51,775
I wouldn't put it past them to steal that, too.

332
00:14:51,975 --> 00:14:52,712
What's going on?

333
00:14:53,916 --> 00:14:56,808
- Oh my God.
- Fran.

334
00:14:57,084 --> 00:14:59,118
- Poor thing.
- I don't believe it.

335
00:14:59,280 --> 00:15:01,560
- Such a great lady.
- Great lady.

336
00:15:01,924 --> 00:15:04,170
Eighty-three on her last birthday.

337
00:15:04,442 --> 00:15:07,049
- A good long life.
- We should all be so lucky.

338
00:15:07,187 --> 00:15:08,647
- I'm gonna miss her.
- Me, too.

339
00:15:12,104 --> 00:15:14,180
- So...
- Yeah?

340
00:15:14,325 --> 00:15:17,182
I guess this'll put that old inn of hers on the market.

341
00:15:17,315 --> 00:15:20,546
Right. I mean, she wanted to keep it as long as she was alive, and now...

342
00:15:21,148 --> 00:15:23,495
- Oh my God.
- What?

343
00:15:23,643 --> 00:15:26,813
You don't think that because we wanted the property so much, we killed Fran.

344
00:15:26,896 --> 00:15:28,800
- What?
- Through the power of our minds.

345
00:15:28,907 --> 00:15:31,135
No, no, we wished for the property, not this!

346
00:15:31,262 --> 00:15:32,620
Yeah, but you never know with karma.

347
00:15:32,784 --> 00:15:35,457
- Look, we loved Fran, right?
- Yes, we did.

348
00:15:35,528 --> 00:15:37,847
And whether or not we get the Dragonfly Inn has nothing to do

349
00:15:37,920 --> 00:15:39,384
with her dying right now.

350
00:15:39,630 --> 00:15:41,186
Right... sort of.

351
00:15:41,283 --> 00:15:42,994
Besides, we don't know what's happening with the inn.

352
00:15:43,136 --> 00:15:44,820
- Fran has no heirs.
- You never know.

353
00:15:44,965 --> 00:15:47,627
Some long lost gold-toothed cousin could come out of the woodwork,

354
00:15:47,832 --> 00:15:51,416
inherit it and turn it into a beauty salon or law offices.

355
00:15:51,513 --> 00:15:52,573
Not our Dragonfly!

356
00:15:52,758 --> 00:15:55,196
The point is, if we are meant to have the Dragonfly Inn,

357
00:15:55,317 --> 00:15:57,746
- then we are meant to have it.
- Right. Like Doris Day.

358
00:15:57,904 --> 00:15:59,009
- Que sera.
- Sera.

359
00:15:59,369 --> 00:16:01,816
Let's focus on Fran and how much we loved her.

360
00:16:02,067 --> 00:16:04,049
- Not think about the inn at all.
- Okay.

361
00:16:05,774 --> 00:16:06,864
You're thinking about it.

362
00:16:06,957 --> 00:16:08,477
Just about where to put the woodburning oven.

363
00:16:08,564 --> 00:16:10,458
We'll put it in the apartment that we're sharing in hell.

364
00:16:10,596 --> 00:16:13,045
- Let's buy flowers.
- Yeah, lots and lots of flowers.

365
00:16:17,191 --> 00:16:18,615
This is a really nice chair.

366
00:16:20,249 --> 00:16:22,116
- Is it old?
- Old enough.

367
00:16:22,655 --> 00:16:25,174
Well, it's really nice. I mean, the back is very sturdy

368
00:16:25,261 --> 00:16:27,964
and the legs are all the same length and the wood looks like

369
00:16:28,037 --> 00:16:32,122
it was a tree at some point, which is good for wood, 'cause it was.

370
00:16:32,997 --> 00:16:33,945
Could you get that please?

371
00:16:34,456 --> 00:16:34,949
Yes, Mama.

372
00:16:40,090 --> 00:16:41,883
- What are you doing here?
- I'm here to see your mother.

373
00:16:41,968 --> 00:16:43,090
- What?
- Excuse me.

374
00:16:43,274 --> 00:16:44,196
Dave, Dave, wait!

375
00:16:46,306 --> 00:16:48,216
Excuse me, Mrs. Kim, I need to speak with you.

376
00:16:48,343 --> 00:16:49,126
I'm busy, David.

377
00:16:49,261 --> 00:16:51,646
A few weeks ago you told me that Lane had a crush on me.

378
00:16:51,893 --> 00:16:53,643
Well, I have a crush on her, too.

379
00:16:53,735 --> 00:16:56,372
Now, I know you have very strict rules about dating and boys,

380
00:16:56,536 --> 00:16:58,922
but I just want you to know that I'm a good person.

381
00:16:59,102 --> 00:17:01,754
I don't smoke, I don't drink, I've never gotten a ticket,

382
00:17:01,882 --> 00:17:04,441
I'm healthy, I take care of myself, I floss.

383
00:17:04,575 --> 00:17:07,206
I never watch more than 30 minutes of television a night partly

384
00:17:07,299 --> 00:17:10,580
because I think it's a waste of time and partly because there's nothing on.

385
00:17:10,760 --> 00:17:13,218
I respect my parents, I do well in school,

386
00:17:13,335 --> 00:17:15,681
I never play video games in case they do someday prove

387
00:17:15,748 --> 00:17:17,668
that playing them can turn you into a serial killer.

388
00:17:17,810 --> 00:17:21,497
I don't drink coffee. I hate soda because the carbonation freaks me out.

389
00:17:21,685 --> 00:17:24,252
I'm happy to give up meat if you feel strongly about it.

390
00:17:24,364 --> 00:17:25,639
I don't mind wearing a tie.

391
00:17:25,772 --> 00:17:28,379
I enjoy playing those hymns on my guitar,

392
00:17:28,522 --> 00:17:31,840
and I really, really want to take your daughter to the prom.

393
00:17:37,586 --> 00:17:38,229
Mrs. Kim?

394
00:17:39,976 --> 00:17:41,805
Please don't make me repeat that list again.

395
00:17:44,770 --> 00:17:47,277
Let never day nor night unhallow'd pass,

396
00:17:47,708 --> 00:17:50,238
but still remember what the Lord hath done.

397
00:17:52,070 --> 00:17:54,860
Okay, thank you.

398
00:18:04,176 --> 00:18:05,531
- Did you hear what she said?
- Yes, I did.

399
00:18:05,675 --> 00:18:06,813
- What did it mean?
- I don't know.

400
00:18:06,976 --> 00:18:08,952
- Was it a yes, was it a no?
- I'm not sure.

401
00:18:09,079 --> 00:18:11,559
Well, it's gotta be from the bible, right? So I'll just go home, do some research,

402
00:18:11,671 --> 00:18:14,022
look on the Internet, see what I can find. I'll call you when I know something.

403
00:18:14,493 --> 00:18:15,082
Okay.

404
00:18:21,707 --> 00:18:23,048
I'm so writing him a song tonight.

405
00:18:37,359 --> 00:18:38,614
Left your wallet in the diner.

406
00:18:40,529 --> 00:18:41,845
Oh, wow, did I?

407
00:18:42,752 --> 00:18:44,932
Look at that. I guess I did. Thanks for bringing it back.

408
00:18:45,070 --> 00:18:45,727
No problem.

409
00:18:46,007 --> 00:18:48,389
You know, I really like this driver's license picture, too,

410
00:18:48,461 --> 00:18:50,458
so you could imagine what a drag it would be to have to replace it.

411
00:18:50,555 --> 00:18:51,481
So what are you doing here, Jimmy?

412
00:18:51,691 --> 00:18:53,975
- Just passing through.
- Passing through from where?

413
00:18:54,139 --> 00:18:56,085
- California.
- California?

414
00:18:56,336 --> 00:18:58,845
Yeah, I've been there for a few years now, seems to be working out.

415
00:18:58,931 --> 00:19:00,687
- Well, glad to hear it.
- Yeah.

416
00:19:00,979 --> 00:19:04,175
- So what are you doing here, Jimmy?
- Nothing, really, just...

417
00:19:04,291 --> 00:19:06,268
- He hasn't missed you.
- I'm sure that he hasn't.

418
00:19:06,417 --> 00:19:08,537
- Never says a word about you.
- I wouldn't expect he would.

419
00:19:08,639 --> 00:19:10,350
Do you know why he doesn't miss you, Jimmy?

420
00:19:10,452 --> 00:19:13,724
Because you're a loser and nobody missed a loser.

421
00:19:13,847 --> 00:19:15,158
It's been seventeen years, Luke.

422
00:19:15,270 --> 00:19:17,246
Oh, you remember how long it's been. I am impressed.

423
00:19:17,374 --> 00:19:18,639
Yeah, well, I always could count.

424
00:19:18,722 --> 00:19:20,191
And your list of attributes ends there.

425
00:19:20,339 --> 00:19:22,330
Okay, so I guess we're not playing nice anymore.

426
00:19:22,475 --> 00:19:26,151
You know, the last time I saw you is right after Liz gave birth.

427
00:19:26,263 --> 00:19:28,430
You were gonna go out and buy some diapers

428
00:19:28,526 --> 00:19:30,350
and meet us back at the apartment. Remember that?

429
00:19:30,441 --> 00:19:30,846
Yes.

430
00:19:30,994 --> 00:19:33,083
You went out, but you never came back.

431
00:19:33,257 --> 00:19:35,993
A lot of time has passed and a lot of things have changed.

432
00:19:36,135 --> 00:19:37,779
Really, like what things? You?

433
00:19:37,881 --> 00:19:39,766
Yes, me. Maybe. Why not?

434
00:19:39,878 --> 00:19:41,773
Oh, come on, you never called before. Why now?

435
00:19:41,839 --> 00:19:43,273
- What do you want, you need money?
- What?

436
00:19:43,375 --> 00:19:45,008
- 'Cause he doesn't have any.
- I don't need money.

437
00:19:45,111 --> 00:19:46,888
- I don't have any either.
- I don't need money.

438
00:19:47,016 --> 00:19:48,594
So the look is a choice?

439
00:19:48,690 --> 00:19:51,747
No, I just wanted to... I don't know, see him.

440
00:19:51,880 --> 00:19:53,151
- Why now?
- I don't know,

441
00:19:53,391 --> 00:19:55,751
I just thought it was time. You don't think it was time?

442
00:19:55,895 --> 00:19:57,604
You really want my opinion on this subject?

443
00:19:57,717 --> 00:19:59,786
- Luke, give me a break.
- Give you a break?

444
00:19:59,949 --> 00:20:02,253
I am trying to keep this kid from falling off the face of the Earth.

445
00:20:02,337 --> 00:20:04,384
I'm trying to get him through school. I'm trying to give him a future.

446
00:20:04,481 --> 00:20:07,549
And I gotta be totally honest with you, Jimmy - I am not doing too well.

447
00:20:07,655 --> 00:20:07,985
No?

448
00:20:08,051 --> 00:20:12,048
No, and the last thing he needs is a special appearance by his father

449
00:20:12,167 --> 00:20:14,240
who can't be here for any good reason.

450
00:20:14,349 --> 00:20:17,210
There's no evil plan here. I have a job, a life.

451
00:20:17,369 --> 00:20:19,213
- I just thought I'd come and...
- What? Say hello,

452
00:20:19,284 --> 00:20:21,266
- see if he looks like you? Then what?
- Well...

453
00:20:21,368 --> 00:20:22,403
- What?
- I don't know!

454
00:20:22,514 --> 00:20:25,429
Okay, well, while you're figuring it out, let me plant this little thought in your head -

455
00:20:25,506 --> 00:20:29,152
you do or say anything to upset Jess and make it harder for me

456
00:20:29,264 --> 00:20:32,043
to keep him on the right path, I'm gonna put your head through a wall.

457
00:20:32,157 --> 00:20:35,650
Any wall, you can pick the wall, but it's gonna be a wall, okay?

458
00:20:38,332 --> 00:20:39,935
I just wanted to see him.

459
00:20:40,774 --> 00:20:43,667
Well, you saw him. Now get outta here.

460
00:20:50,443 --> 00:20:53,199
You know, Fran was one of the first people I met when we moved here.

461
00:20:53,266 --> 00:20:53,896
I know.

462
00:20:54,325 --> 00:20:55,898
The first day here, I stopped in...

463
00:20:56,016 --> 00:20:57,454
And asked her for directions to the inn.

464
00:20:57,598 --> 00:21:01,632
Yeah. She was so sweet. And oh my God, she loved you.

465
00:21:01,873 --> 00:21:04,807
I didn't think she was gonna let me leave the bakery with you.

466
00:21:05,657 --> 00:21:08,186
She just kept giving you cookies in a shameless attempt

467
00:21:08,294 --> 00:21:10,308
to buy your affections away from me. And let me tell you,

468
00:21:10,421 --> 00:21:13,361
for a couple weeks, it worked. For two weeks, you just kept staring at me like,

469
00:21:13,501 --> 00:21:16,773
"You're the lady who took me away from the cookies. I'm gonna kill you."

470
00:21:16,922 --> 00:21:19,194
Mom, can I just meet you at the church?

471
00:21:19,810 --> 00:21:21,765
